from typing import List

class Solution:
    def kidsWithCandies(self, candies: List[int], extraCandies: int) -> List[bool]:
        max_candies = max(candies)
        result = []
        for candy in candies:
            if candy + extraCandies >= max_candies:
                result.append(True)
            else:
                result.append(False)
        return result
```

This solution first determines the maximum number of candies any single kid currently has. It then iterates through the list of candies, checking if giving each kid all the extra candies would result in them having at least as many candies as the current maximum. The result is a list of booleans indicating whether this condition is met for each kid.
